    xml:id="ch_dashboard">
    <title>Dashboard</title>
    
    <section>
        <title>Main panel</title>
    <para>
        The Sirocco dashboard provides a unified interface to control resources deployed on multiple cloud providers.
        <figure xml:id="dashboard-main">
            <title>Dashboard main screen</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="figures/dashboard_main_screen.png"
                        format="PNG" contentwidth="6in"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </para>
    <para>The left panel gives access to the main resources managed by Sirocco:</para>
    <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>Providers</guilabel></term>
            <listitem>
                <para>View the IaaS providers accessible to the current tenant</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>Instances</guilabel></term>
            <listitem>
                <para>View the VM instances</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>Images</guilabel></term>
            <listitem>
                <para>View VM images</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>Volumes</guilabel></term>
            <listitem>
                <para>View the volumes providing persistent block storage for instances</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>Networks</guilabel></term>
            <listitem>
                <para>View networks and their subnets</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>External IP addresses</guilabel></term>
            <listitem>
                <para>View the external IP addresses and manage their association to instances</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>Keypairs</guilabel></term>
            <listitem>
                <para>View SSH keypairs whose public key can be injected into a VM to provide password-less login</para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Adding a provider</title>
        <para>Click on the "Add provider" button on the Provider view to add a provider:
            
            <figure xml:id="dashboard-provider-choice">
                <title>Dashboard provider creation</title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/dashboard_provider_choice.png"
                            format="PNG" contentwidth="6in"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
            The following snapshots shows the parameters required to add a provider account on the following IaaS providers:
        </para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem><para>Amazon EC2</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>OpenStack</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>VMware vCloud Director</para></listitem>
            <listitem><para>Microsoft SPF/SCVMM</para></listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para>
            
